After your order is shipped, we will forward the tracking number so you can follow your package which will update with an ETA on delivery. At this time we don't ship internationally.

Please let me know how I can assist you further today, I'm just a text away!

send_to_cs: Send to CS for post purchase issues, use PPI shortcut
escalate: Add phone# in the ESC notes
tone: ðŸ…¿ When suggesting a product, add "we have other available in that category here-" then send the whole category.
dos_and_don_ts: Don't mention Extended Warranty for existing orders, it can't be purchased or added retroactively
promo_and_promo_exclusions: Check the brand website for the most up to date holiday promotions

â†’ Inquire what exact brush/product they have
â†’ Provide any user guides available

tone: Keep messages shorter and more direct

templates: If the cx asks where there order is, and it's a confirmed order within the standard processing and shipping time, only share the "Order status/order tracking" temp

For product complaints/bad experiences use PBE shortcut

If cx is a short amount away from reaching the $100 threshold for the welcome discount to apply use SRT shortcut
If cx ask why their order was canceled, use MOC shortcut
If cx purchased from their dentist and looking for rebate ($30, $20, $10 back) use RBT shortcut
For post-purchase issues with Amazon orders, use PS shortcut

drive_to_purchase: For general recommendations use CFR shortcut
Always refer cxs to iO series products, when possible
promo_and_promo_exclusions: The $85 welcome promo code isn't for % off, once applied a free item is added to the cart

send_to_cs: Send to CS for order status updates
Send to CS if there's a pending ESC and cx ask for an update (even if it's been less than 2 business days)
escalate: ESC immediately if the customer wants an order to arrive at a specific time, or before our standard shipping time
ESC for product info that you can't find on the site
tone: Close the convo once the client takes over
templates: If cx sends us their measurements or asks about making a custom sizing order use the CUS template.
If cx mentions that they're going to lose weight, use 'Lose weight' template.
dos_and_don_ts: Do not recommend the customer go to a place to get measured
"@ The Vault" items are designated for returns/exchanges, but may also be available in other sizes on The Vault website. Always check there first
When the color is closer to white and not cream we say off white
You should never direct the customer to the sizing chart when they mention custom sizing or they send their measurements
Don't tell the customer to hold off on purchase if they are going to lose weight.
drive_to_purchase: When recommending products, make sure they're aligned with the colors, style the cx is looking for
promo_and_promo_exclusions: If cx ask about pricing, tell them to add items to their cart and the best discount will apply automatically
The 40% discount applies automatically when cx add five or more items to their cart
If cx going to purchase a lot of products in one purchase, share with them what you can find on current offer page along with the link: https://www.sebastiancruzcouture.com/pages/current-offers
